table_caption: Brain locations where clusters of significant differences between groups were found for FW maps analysis at p < 0.01 (FWE corrected).
table_foot: % columns indicate the percent volume of the cluster inside the corresponding brain area. Only clusters with higher FW values in AD than HC were observed.For JHU white-matter tractography atlas: ATR anterior thalamic radiation, CST cortical spinal tract, CGC cingulum (cingulate gyrus part), CGH cingulum (hippocampal part), IFOF inferior fronto-occipital fasciculus, ILF inferior longitudinal fasciculus, SLF superior longitudinal fasciculus, UF uncinate fasciculus. For ICBM-DTI-81 white-matter atlas: CC corpus callosum, CP cerebral peduncle, LIC limb of internal capsule, IC internal capsule, CR corona radiata, SS sagittal stratum, EC external capsule.
